comments: DeRozan (CHI) makes contact to LeVert's (IND) arm that causes him to lose control of the ball.
Holiday (IND) braces for the contact with DeRozan (CHI) with two forearms slightly extended but the marginal contact does not affect DeRozan's pass.
Craig (IND) makes marginal contact with LaVine (CHI) that does not affect his dunk attempt.
Sabonis (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Green's (CHI) path and the two players briefly engage as Green goes underneath the screen.
Green (CHI) moves into LeVert's (IND) arm/body and initiates contact that affects his shot attempt at the rim.
DeRozan (CHI) spins away from the marginal contact by Craig (IND) prior to the shot attempt.
Brissett (IND) makes incidental contact with White (CHI) as he elevates for the rebound.
DeRozan (CHI) brings his arms forward and makes contact to LeVert's (IND) head that affects his shot attempt at the rim.
Sabonis (IND) briefly places a hand on LaVine's (CHI) non-shooting arm and makes marginal contact to his side that does not affect the shot attempt at the rim.
Brissett (IND) makes marginal contact with LaVine's (CHI) non-shooting arm that does not affect his shot attempt at the rim.
LaVine (CHI) leaves his feet and returns to the floor without having released the ball.
LeVert (IND) places his off-arm against Dosunmu (CHI) and releases from the contact as he steps back.

DeRozan (CHI) initiates body contact with Craig (IND) that affects his ability to control the loose ball.  The ball then goes out of bounds off of Craig's leg, although possession is incorrectly awarded to the Pacers.
DeRozan (CHI) cleanly deflects the throw-in near the basket.
Dosunmu (CHI) places a forearm against LeVert's (IND) side and the marginal contact does not affect his ability to elevate for the throw-in.
White (CHI) gains possession of the loose ball on the floor and does not commit a traveling violation.
Craig (IND) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
